Global Smart Drugs Market Insights
Smart Drugs Market size was valued at USD 8.2 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 22.5 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 16.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Smart Drugs Market Overview
The Smart Drugs market is poised for significant growth, projected to reach a market value of USD 8.25 billion by 2030, with a robust CAGR of 12.6% from 2022 to 2030. Smart Drugs, also known as nootropics or cognitive enhancers, are substances that improve cognitive function, including memory, focus, creativity, and overall mental performance. With the increasing demand for cognitive performance improvements in both academic and professional settings, the market is expanding. The adoption of smart drugs is becoming more prevalent in healthcare, research, and lifestyle management. Furthermore, advancements in neuroscience and biotechnology are enabling the development of more efficient and targeted nootropic substances, fueling market growth.

